@startuml Workflow_Traceability_Control_Centric_Swimlane
title Control-Centric Bundling - Traceability Workflow (Swimlane)

participant "Compliance Officer" as CO
participant "Developer" as DEV
participant "Governance\nConfiguration" as GC
participant "Traceability\nService" as TS
participant "Cloud\nPlatform" as CP
database "Control\nMapping Store" as CMS

== Control Mapping Phase ==
activate CO
CO -> DEV: Define Controls from Regulation
deactivate CO

activate DEV
DEV -> DEV: Extract Controls\n(e.g., C-001, C-002, etc.)
note right of DEV
  For each control:
  - Control ID
  - Description
  - Regulatory requirement
end note

DEV -> GC: Map Control → Platform Policies\n(1:1 or 1:n)
activate GC
GC -> CMS: Store Control-Policy Mappings
note right of CMS
  Example:
  C-001 → [Policy-A, Policy-B]
  C-002 → [Policy-C]
end note
deactivate GC
deactivate DEV

== LZ Blueprint Selection ==
activate CO
CO -> CO: Select required Controls\nbased on workload
note right of CO
  Decision: Baseline Level
  - No protection
  - Standard protection
  - High protection
end note
deactivate CO

== Deployment Phase ==
activate DEV
DEV -> TS: Deploy LZ with selected Controls\n[C-001, C-003, C-005]
deactivate DEV

activate TS
TS -> CMS: Lookup Platform Policies\nfor each Control
activate CMS
CMS --> TS: Return Policy bundles
deactivate CMS

TS -> CP: Apply Policies to resources
activate CP
CP -> CP: Deploy Policy-A, Policy-B, Policy-C
CP -> CP: Tag resources with\nControl IDs
note right of CP
  Resource metadata:
  - Control-ID: C-001
  - Resource-ID: res-123
  - Timestamp
  - Enforcement status
end note
deactivate CP

TS -> TS: Record traceability mapping:\nControl → Resource\n(bidirectional index)
deactivate TS

== Audit & Verification ==
activate CO
CO -> TS: "Audit: Show all\nimplemented Controls"
note right of CO
  Compliance verification query
end note
deactivate CO

activate TS
TS -> TS: Query traceability index:\nFetch all Control→Resource mappings
note right of TS
  **Index Structure:**
  - Bidirectional mapping stored at deployment
  - Control ID → [Resource IDs, Policy IDs]
  - Resource ID → Control ID (reverse lookup)
  
  **Query Operation:**
  1. Retrieve all stored Control→Resource edges
  2. Group resources by Control ID
  3. Aggregate policy enforcement status
  
  **Trivial Lookup Rationale:**
  - Direct 1:1 index (not search)
  - Pre-computed at deployment time
  - Time Complexity: O(1) or O(log n)
  - No need to traverse policies or components
end note

TS -> CP: Verify compliance:\nCheck if resources\nstill comply with Controls
activate CP
CP -> CP: Verify policy enforcement
CP -> CP: Get compliance status\nper Control per Resource
deactivate CP

TS -> TS: Generate audit report:\n- Control ID\n- Associated Policies\n- Deployed Resources\n- Compliance Status
note right of TS
  **Report Structure (per Control):**
  
  Control: C-001 (Encryption at Rest)
  ├─ Policies: [Policy-A, Policy-B]
  ├─ Resources: [res-123, res-456]
  └─ Status: ✓ Compliant
  
  Control: C-003 (MFA Enforcement)
  ├─ Policies: [Policy-C]
  ├─ Resources: [res-789]
  └─ Status: ✓ Compliant
  
  **Key Advantage:**
  Clear 1:1 traceability from Regulation
  → Control → Policies → Resources
end note
TS --> CO: Audit Report
note right of TS
  Complete traceability:
  Regulation → Control → Policies → Resources
  Status: ✓ Compliant
end note
deactivate TS

@enduml
